article_title: MD Anderson to expand its cancer care network
article_text: To continue reading this story, you will need to be a digital subscriber to HoustonChronicle.com.

article_metadata.description: University of Texas MD Anderson Cancer Center announced expansion plans Thursday with two new locations in the Houston metro area, according to a pair of news releases.  "Together with the services that we provide, this collaboration further expands the excellent health care services that will be available at the league City campus," Donna Sollenberger, executive vice president and CEO of UTMB Health, said in a statement.
article_metadata.author.name: By Jenny Deam
